## Steps Performed

1. Added PC1, PC2, and one switch to create a direct network.
2. Connected both PCs to the switch using straight-through cables.
3. Assigned IP addresses to both PCs in the same subnet.
4. Switched to Simulation Mode.
5. Sent a ping from PC1 to PC2 and observed the ICMP Echo Request and Echo Reply.
6. Added another switch between PC1 and PC2 to create an extra hop.
7. Repeated the ping from PC1 to PC2.
8. Observed the additional forwarding step in the packet path.
9. Compared the delay and packet movement in both setups.
